"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-she-was-good-spain-coach-hails-super-falcons-star\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Spain coach, Montserrat Tom\\u00e9 has hailed Super Falcons goalkeeper, Chiamaka Nnadozie for her impressive display during both sides' Paris 2024 Olympic clash at the weekend.  Nnadozie made some fantastic saves to keep the scoreline level until the closing minutes.  Nigeria had chances to break the deadlock before Alexia Putellas' winner but failed to score as the match ended 1-0 in favour of Spain.  The Super Falcons had problems with their finishing, with captain Rasheedat Ajibade spurning two gilt-edged chances.  Speaking to reporters after the game against Nigeria, Tome praises Nnadozie.  \\\"I am very happy. They had already ruled out a goal by Salma, which was offside. We had chances, Aitana had them, Alexia had them too, others,\\\" Tome said.  \\\"We knew that Nnadozie was a good goalkeeper. In addition, her style of play conditioned us a lot because of the long shots she has.\\\"  Preseason: Mbappe, Bellingham missing as Real Madrid squad land in US  NPFL: Akwa United to participate in Bayelsa pre-season tournament  Israel-US war in Iran illegal, causing damage to civilians - Spain's PM Sanchez  Spain's PM Sanchez urges end to UN Security Council veto power, blasts US for global conflicts  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  War: Macron backs Spain amid Trump's threats over base denial  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"